VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bSELECT\s+?\*?\s+?FROM\s+[^\s]+\s+(WHERE|ORDER BY)\b.*
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(\+|`|\$\{|req\.|params|query|body) && MISSING:(\?|prepare|bind|replacements|sequelize\.query\s*\(.*replacements)
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects SELECT statements with WHERE or ORDER BY clauses in SQL queries, which may be vulnerable to SQL injection if user input is not handled securely in JavaScript environments.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: SELECT Statements with WHERE or ORDER BY.
